# Flyway Migrations

Use Flyway (SQL-based) instead of Alembic for schema migrations.

## Structure

```
db/
  migration/
    V1__create_tables.sql
    V2__add_column.sql
```

- Naming: `V<version>__<description>.sql` (double underscore).
- Version: integer or dotted (e.g. `V1`, `V1_1`, `V2`).

## Execution (Flyway CLI)

```bash
flyway -url=$DATABASE_URL -locations=filesystem:db/migration migrate
```

- Download Flyway CLI or use Docker: `flyway/flyway` image.
- For PostgreSQL, URL format: `jdbc:postgresql://host:5432/dbname` (Flyway uses JDBC; for CLI, `-url` accepts same format with `jdbc:` prefix — check Flyway docs for exact syntax).

## Docker

- **Option A**: Use `flyway/flyway` image, mount migrations, pass `DATABASE_URL` as env.
- **Option B**: Add Flyway CLI to app image; run `flyway migrate` in migration job.

## Azure migration job

Replace Alembic command with Flyway. Sample: one-shot Container App Job with `flyway/flyway` image:

```hcl
command = ["flyway", "-url=${var.database_connection_string}", "-locations=filesystem:/flyway/sql", "migrate"]
```

Mount migrations into `/flyway/sql` or bake into image. Convert `postgresql://` to `jdbc:postgresql://` if Flyway expects JDBC URL.

